Prerequisites

Three EC2 instances (RHEL)
Instances deployed within the same VPC
SSH access using a PEM key
Amazon EFS File System
EFS Security Group allowing NFS access (TCP 2049)

EFS Details
Parameter	Value
File System ID	fs-0743fa78e8d7ca1f1
Mount Path	/home/ec2-user/shared
Protocol	NFSv4.1
Encryption	TLS
Security Group Configuration
EC2 Security Group
Type	Port	Source
SSH	22	Administrator IP
EFS Security Group
Type	Port	Source
NFS	2049	EC2 Security Group

Note: For learning purposes, 0.0.0.0/0 can be used temporarily. In production environments, restrict access to the EC2 Security Group.

Installation Steps
1. Install EFS Utilities
sudo yum install -y amazon-efs-utils

Verify installation:

which mount.efs

Expected output:

/usr/sbin/mount.efs
2. Create Mount Directory
sudo mkdir -p /home/ec2-user/shared
3. Mount EFS
sudo mount -t efs fs-0743fa78e8d7ca1f1:/ /home/ec2-user/shared
4. Verify Mount
mount | grep shared

Expected output:

127.0.0.1:/ on /home/ec2-user/shared type nfs4 (...)
5. Test Shared Storage

Create a file:

echo "Hello from Prod" > /home/ec2-user/shared/prod.txt

Verify:

ls -l /home/ec2-user/shared
cat /home/ec2-user/shared/prod.txt
Configure Automatic Mounting

Edit /etc/fstab:

sudo vi /etc/fstab

Add the following line:

fs-0743fa78e8d7ca1f1:/ /home/ec2-user/shared efs defaults,_netdev,tls 0 0

Save and exit.

Validate /etc/fstab
sudo mount -a

No output indicates successful validation.

Verify Persistence After Reboot
sudo reboot

After reconnecting:

mount | grep shared
ls /home/ec2-user/shared

Expected output:

127.0.0.1:/ on /home/ec2-user/shared type nfs4 (...)
prod.txt
